main event: Two luminous objects were observed maintaining the same relative position at an elevation of 25 degrees.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be rotated on top and flat on bottom.
One object appeared smaller and slightly fainter than the other.
No sound was heard from the objects.
The objects were observed for approximately 20 minutes, but did not disappear during this time.
A retired USAF colonel with over 7,000 flying hours identified the objects as celestial bodies, likely planets, due to the clear atmosphere following a cold front.
photographs: No, the report does not include any photographs
